  "commentary": "With SPX at 6956.51 sitting just above the massive +22.3B gamma wall at 6950, dealers are actively selling rallies into this level to hedge their long gamma positions. The PIN regime with 141B total GEX creates a strong gravitational pull toward 6950, with dealers providing natural resistance on any push higher and support on dips back toward the 6900 level. Key levels to watch are the 6950 max gamma strike acting as immediate resistance and the GEX flip at 6848 - any break below flip turns dealers from stabilizers into momentum sellers.\n\nBottom line: expect price to grind sideways around 6950 with limited upside.",
